Alcolock should prevent this from happening because it is a system connected to a vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents the car from starting up if the driver does not breathe before, or if it is recorded above the permitted concentration of alcohol.
Its price exceeds EUR 1 000 and would have to be paid by the culprit himself.
